name: waveorder
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "waveorder" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0b0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/waveorder-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2bb0c2d94eb820f6dc386f65b9b1064020652b9f63dfce06fba952fe641bba55
  patches:
    - setup.patch

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.7
  run:
    - ipywidgets >=7.5.1
    - matplotlib-base >=3.1.1
    - natsort >=7.1.1
    - numpy >=1.17.4
    - opencv >=3.4.1
    - python >=3.7
    - pywavelets >=1.1.1
    - scipy >=1.3.0
    - tifffile >=2020.11.26
    - zarr >=2.6.1

test:
  imports:
    - waveorder
  commands:
    - pip list
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/mehta-lab/waveorder/
  summary: wave optical simulations and deconvolution of optical properties
  license: LicenseRef-Chan-Zuckerberg-Biohub
  license_file: LICENSE.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - talonchandler
    - mattersoflight
    - goanpeca
